nternal\n| colspan=3 | 16&nbsp;GB, 32&nbsp;GB, or 64&nbsp;GB\n|-\n! External\n| colspan=3 {{N/A}}\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Camera\n! Back\n| {{n/a}}\n| colspan=2 | 8&nbsp;[[Megapixels|MP]]\n|-\n! Front\n| colspan=3 | 1.2&nbsp;[[Megapixels|MP]] [[High-definition video|HD]] 720p still and video camera\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Microphone\n| colspan=3 | Yes\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Bluetooth\n| colspan=3 | BT 4.0 + EDR (HID and A2DP profiles only)\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Wireless\n! [[Wi-Fi]]\n| colspan=2 | Dual-band 802.11&nbsp;a/b/g/n\n| colspan=1 | Dual-band 802.11&nbsp;a/b/g/n/ac<br />MIMO + HT80\n|-\n! +Cellular\n| colspan=3 | adds 4G LTE\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Location\n! Wi-Fi\n| colspan=\"3\" | Wi-Fi based\n|-\n! +Cellular\n| colspan=\"3\" | adds [[Global Positioning System | GPS]] and [[assisted_GPS | aGPS]]<ref name=\"firespecs\"/><ref>{{Cite web|title = Fire HDX 8.9 product page |url = https://www.amazon.com/Fire-HDX-8-9-Display-Wi-Fi/dp/B00HCNHDN0|website = www.amazon.com|accessdate = 2015-11-28}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Proximity\n! Wi-Fi\n| colspan=\"3\" {{n/a}}\n|-\n! +Cellular\n| colspan=2 | Yes\n| colspan=\"1\" {{n/a}}\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Compass\n! Wi-Fi\n| colspan=\"3\" {{n/a}}\n|-\n! +Cellular\n| colspan=\"3\" rowspan=\"4\" | Yes\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Light sensor\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Accelerometer\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Gyroscope \n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" | Barometer\n| colspan=\"3\" {{n/a}}\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Weight\n! Wi-Fi\n| {{convert|303|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| {{convert|374|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| {{convert|375|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n|-\n! +Cellular\n| {{convert|311|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| {{convert|384|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n| {{convert|389|g|oz|abbr=on}}\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Dimensions\n| {{convert|186|x|128|x|9.0|mm|in|abbr=on|disp=br()}} \n| colspan=2 | {{convert|231|x|158|x|7.8|mm|in|abbr=on|disp=br()}}\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Battery\n| 4500<ref>{{cite web|author=Kindle Fire HDX 7&quot; |url=https://www.ifixit.com/Teardown/Kindle+Fire+HDX+7-Inch+Teardown/18351/ |title=Kindle Fire HDX 7\" Teardown |publisher=iFixit |date=2013-10-14 |accessdate=2013-11-27}}</ref>&nbsp;mAh \n| colspan=2 | Up to 12 hours\n|}\n\n== Reception ==\n[[Engadget]] gave the Fire HDX an 85 out of 100, saying that it may be the most compelling case for Amazon's tablet [[Closed platform|ecosystem]]. While advanced users may be turned off by the limited app selection, the display's gorgeous color accuracy may make the tablet a good buy for everyone else, especially Amazon Prime members.<ref>{{cite web|author=Engadget |url=https://www.engadget.com/2013/12/31/2013-engadget-reviews/ |title=The year in reviews: 2013's best and worst gadgets scored and scrutinized |publisher=Engadget.com |date= |accessdate=2013-12-31}}</ref>\n\n[[PC Magazine]] gave the Amazon Kindle Fire HDX 7\" (Wi-Fi) edition 4 out of 5 and rated \"Excellent\" while following pros were noted: \"Sharp screen. Fast processor. Extremely easy to use. Amazing live tech support.\"<ref name=\"pcmag\"/>\n\nThe Fire HDX's screen has high color accuracy and high pixel density at 339&nbsp;PPI, and as of early 2013 was one of the highest of tablet devices commercially available.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.displaymate.com/Tablet_ShootOut_3.htm |title=Flagship Tablet Display Technology Shoot-Out |publisher=Displaymate.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-27}}</ref>  However, [[CNET]] pointed out that no [[Google Play]] access means limited app selection compared to other Android tablets and some users may be bothered by an additional $15 to remove ads on the lock screen, while ads on the home screen can be removed with a system setting.<ref>{{cite web|last=Franklin |first=Eric |url=http://reviews.cnet.com/amazon-kindle-fire-hdx-7-inch/ |title=Amazon Kindle Fire HDX 7 Review - Watch CNET's Video Review |publisher=Reviews.cnet.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-27}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Comparison of tablet computers|Tablet computers]]\n* [[Comparison of e-book readers|E-book readers]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00DOPNO4M/ Official Amazon.com site for 7\" version]\n* [https://www.amazon.com/dp/B00HCNHDN0 Official Amazon.com site for 8.9\" version]\n\n{{Amazon}}\n{{Android tablets}}\n\n[[Category:Amazon hardware|Fire HDX]]\n[[Category:Android (operating system) devices]]\n[[Category:Tablet computers]]\n[[Category:Tablet computers introduced in 2013]]\n[[Category:Touchscreen portable media players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox information appliance\n| name = Amazon Fire HDX\n| logo = \n| image = File:Fire_HDX_7\"_Front.jpg\n| caption = Fire HDX 7\n| developer = [[Amazon.com]]\n| manufacturer = \n| type = [[Tablet computer]]\n| generation = \n| model = \n| partnumber = \n| releasedate = 7\" model October 18, 2013<br /> 8.9\" model November 7, 2013 (USA)\n| status = <!-- if model is discontinued use \"Discontinued\", otherwise, please leave blank -->\n| unitssold = \n| unitsshipped = \n| media = \n| os = [[Fire OS]] 3, upgradable to Fire OS 5\n| soc = Qualcomm [[Snapdragon 800]]\n| cpu = [[Multi-core processor|Quad-core]] 2.2 GHz [[ARM architecture|ARM]] [[Krait (CPU)|Krait 400]]\n| graphics = Adreno 330\n| storage = 16/32/64&nbsp;[[Gigabyte|GB]]\n| display = '''7\" model:'''<br/> 1920&nbsp;\u00d7&nbsp;1200&nbsp;[[Display resolution|px]] 323&nbsp;[[Pixel density|PPI]]<br/>{{convert|7|in|cm|abbr=on}} diagonal<br/>'''8.9\" model:'''<br/>2560&nbsp;\u00d7&nbsp;1600&nbsp;px 339&nbsp;[[Pixel density|PPI]]<br/>{{convert|8.9|in|cm|abbr=on}} diagonal\n| memory = 2 GB\n| sound = Stereo speakers\n| input = [[GPS]], accelerometer, gyroscope, light sensor\n| camera = Front; '''8.9\" model''' only: 8&nbsp;MP Rear\n| connectivity = Micro-USB 2.0 (type B) <br/>3.5 mm stereo socket<br/>Dual-band 802.11 a/b/g/n WiFi<br/>4G LTE <br/>[[Bluetooth]] 4.0\n| hac = <!-- hearing aid compatibility -->\n| service = Amazon Prime, Amazon Cloud Storage, Amazon Cloud Player, Amazon video, [[Amazon Silk]], Amazon Appstore, Amazon Kindle Store\n| dimensions = '''7\"''' model: 186\u00d7128\u00d79.0&nbsp;mm (7.3\u00d75.0\u00d70.35&nbsp;in) <br/>'''8.9\"''' model: 231\u00d7158\u00d77.8&nbsp;mm (9.1\u00d76.2\u00d70.31&nbsp;in)\n| weight = '''7\" model:'''<br/>WiFi 303&nbsp;g, 4G 311&nbsp;g<br/>'''8.9\" model:'''<br/>WiFi 374&nbsp;g, 4G 384&nbsp;g\n| predecessor = [[Fire HD]]\n| successor = [[Fire HD]]\n| related = \n| website = [https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/B00DOPNO4M/ Amazon Kindle Fire HDX]\n}}\n\nThe '''Fire HDX''', formerly named '''Kindle Fire HDX''', is the high-end model in [[Amazon Fire]] line of [[tablet computer]]s. It was announced on September 25, 2013 and is available in two models, 7&nbsp;inch and 8.9&nbsp;inch. The 7&nbsp;inch WiFi model was released on October 18, 2013 and the 8.9&nbsp;inch WiFi model was released on November 7, 2013 in the United States.\n\nIn September 2014, Amazon released the second generation of the Fire HDX 8.9 model that has a faster processor and a more powerful graphics processing unit. In addition, the name \"Kindle\" was removed from all of the Fire tablets' names.\n\n== Design ==\n\n=== Hardware ===\nBoth the 7&nbsp;inch and 8.9&nbsp;inch [[LCD]] models contain a [[Qualcomm]] [[Snapdragon 800]] processor that has an [[Adreno]] 330 GPU.  The models also have a 1.2&nbsp;megapixel front camera that shoots [[720p]] HD video.  The 8.9&nbsp;inch model has an 8&nbsp;megapixel rear camera that shoots HD [[1080p]] video. The exterior surface has angular, raised plastic edges with the power and volume buttons located on the backside. The Fire HDX features Dolby Digital Plus audio engine powering the two attached speakers. A normal user will get about 12 hours of battery life from a full charge.<ref>{{cite web|last=Kingsley |first=Adrian |url=http://www.zdnet.com/five-ways-the-ipad-is-lagging-behind-the-kindle-fire-hdx_p4-7000025630/#photo |title=Five ways the iPad is lagging behind the Kindle Fire HDX &#124; Page 4 |publisher=ZDNet |date=2014-01-27 |accessdate=2014-02-03}}</ref>\n\nThe Fire HDX 8.9\" refresh in 2014 uses a Qualcomm [[Snapdragon 805]] processor with an Adreno 420 GPU.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rgj.com/story/life/2014/09/24/2014-kindle-fire-hdx-89-preview-technobubble/16140103/|title=Technobubble: Sizing up Amazon's new Kindle Fire HDX 8.9|author=Jason Hidalgo, RGJ|date=24 September 2014}}</ref> The sound system features [[Dolby Atmos]] speaker technology and the Wi-Fi version weighs 13.2 ounces (375 grams).\n\n=== Software ===\nBoth models use [[Fire OS]] 3 which is a [[Proprietary software|proprietary]] [[Fork (software development)|fork]] of [[Android (operating system)|Android]] 4.2.2. It features \"Mayday\", a button for free tech support available any time, \"[[Amazon Silk|Silk]]\", a cloud-accelerated browser, the [[Amazon Appstore]] for games and apps and Amazon.com services for media content purchases.<ref>{{cite web|author=Wilson Rothman |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/technology/amazons-kindle-fire-hdx-tablets-pose-real-threat-ipad-dominance-8C11252610 |title=Amazon's Kindle Fire HDX tablets pose real threat to iPad dominance |publisher=NBC News.com |date=2012-05-18 |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref> The tablets can send video content to a supported TV, game console or through a device like a Wireless Display HDMI adapter wirelessly using \"Second Screen\", but cannot send content via a HDMI cable like its predecessor, the [[Kindle Fire HD]].\n\nThe 2014 refresh uses Fire OS 4 \"Sangria\", which features profiles so each user on the tablet can have their own settings and apps.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.androidguys.com/2014/09/17/whats-new-amazons-fire-os-4-0-sangria/|title=What's new with Amazon's Fire OS 4.0 \"Sangria\"?|work=AndroidGuys}}</ref>\n\n==== Mayday feature ====\nSascha Segan of PC Magazine mentioned: \"Press the Mayday button, and within 15 seconds, a live Amazon operator appears in a video chat window on your screen to answer all of your Kindle Fire questions. He or she will even tell you what apps to download. I've never seen anything else like it on a tablet.\"<ref name=\"pcmag\">{{cite web | title=Hands On With the New Kindle Fires | url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2424815,00.asp|publisher=PC Magazine | accessdate=5 June 2014 | author=Sascha Segan}}</ref> In his review of the Kindle Fire HDX 7\" he called the Mayday remote video support feature as \"revolutionary\" and \"Amazon's most exciting feature\".<ref name=\"pcmag2\">{{cite web | title=Amazon Kindle Fire HDX 7\" (Wi-Fi) |url=https://www.pcmag.com/article2/0,2817,2425068,00.asp| publisher=PC Magazine | accessdate=5 June 2014 | author=Sascha Segan}}</ref>\n\n==== Fire OS UI ====\nThe Fire HDX's UI has a \"Carousel\" which contains the most recent apps used and ones that have been updated or purchased recently.<ref name=\"Using the Carousel, Favorites, and Content Libraries\">{{cite web|title=\"Using the Carousel, Favorites, and Content Libraries\"Amazon.com Help|url=https://www.amazon.com/gp/help/customer/display.html/ref=hp_201008200_content?nodeId=201008200#content|publisher=Amazon|accessdate=20 February 2014}}</ref>  The Carousel also holds documents, videos, music, and books. The  Fire HDX also has a favorites tab in which the user can access the users apps from any other application.\n\n== Models ==\nOverview on generations and models for all Fire tablet devices:\n{{AmazonFireGenerations}}\n\nDetailed specifications for all Fire HDX tagged tablet devices:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Generation <small>(within Fire tablets)</small>\n! colspan=2 | 3rd Generation (2013)\n! colspan=1 | 4th Generation (2014)\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Model !! Kindle Fire HDX (7\") !! Kindle Fire HDX 8.9\" !! Fire HDX 8.9\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Release date\n! Wi-Fi\n| October 18, 2013\n| November 7, 2013\n| October 21, 2014\n|-\n! +Cellular\n| November 14, 2013\n| December 10, 2013\n| December 2014\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Modelnumber\n| KFTHWA (WAN)<br>KFTHWI (Wi-Fi)\n| KFAPWA (WAN)<br>KFAPWI (Wi-Fi